      "content": "hey prof, i'm working on my linguistics paper about language variation and i'm kinda stuck. i have these two short paragraphs from different people. if i were to judge which one sounds more \"intelligent\" or \"competent\" for a university dissertation, which would it be? \n\ntext A: \"The longitudinal study conducted over a five-year period suggests that the socio-economic variables significantly correlate with the developmental outcomes of the subjects in question.\"\n\ntext B: \"We been lookin at how the money situation and where folks live really affects how they grow up and how they doin later on.\"\n\njust curious what you think would look better in a formal paper.",
