      "content": "The perception of capability and education in this context is closely tied to the expectations of the academic genre, not inherently the dialect used. When writing a formal paper, the expectation is adherence to a standard written English register, and deviations like those in Text B are often flagged as informal regardless of the writer's background. However, sociolinguistic analysis recognizes that AAVE and other dialects are rule-governed linguistic systems; the academic judgment is about register suitability, not inherent intelligence.",
