      "content": "It is undeniable that social bias plays a massive role in how these different styles are judged in professional settings. The perception of inferiority often stems from systemic bias embedded within institutional norms, where Standard Academic English is wrongly equated with universal intelligence. Linguistically speaking, AAVE possesses the full grammatical complexity required for high-level thought, utilizing complex syntax and metaphorical structures just as any other language does. Therefore, any perceived difficulty in expressing \"high-level scientific thought\" is primarily a product of prejudice rather than linguistic capacity.",
